Osteoid osteoma -- a rare cause of brachial neuralgia. Osteoid osteoma of the spine causing brachial neuralgia is rare.An adolescent with cervicobrachial neuralgia due to osteoid osteoma of C-4 is presented, and the relevant literature reviewed.The possibility of osteoid osteoma of the cervical spine should be entertained in the differential diagnosis of brachial neuralgia in adolescents.